  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary aim of the study is to identify a predictive molecular signature for response to
      chemotherapy, according to WHO criteria, in patients with non-small cell lung cancer by
      studying the transcriptome (miRNAs and mRNAs) and the single nucleotide polymorphism (SNPs)
      by using high throughput techniques.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
